# ==========================================================================
# Mitigation actions — TRUSTIFAI ontology
#
# Each mitigation has a short description (WithDescription) and a long
# description template (WithLongDescription) stored in the KB.  Templates
# use {operator}, {risk}, {task}, {alternatives} placeholders that are
# interpolated at render time by the backend risk_events module.
#
# Most mitigations will be implemented as graph rewrite rules
# (analogous to dorian/code/parsing/rule.py) that automatically
# transform the pipeline DAG when accepted by the user.
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Mitigation nodes + short + long descriptions ----
# Long descriptions are quoted ("...") to prevent predicate substrings
# (e.g. "is a") inside the text from triggering the parser.

Resampling is a Mitigation
Resampling with description Balance class frequencies via oversampling or undersampling
Resampling with long description "Apply SMOTE or random under-sampling to balance the class distribution before training. Inserts a resampling node into the pipeline after the data split and before {operator}. This directly addresses {risk} by equalising the number of samples across target classes."

Data Augmentation is a Mitigation
Data Augmentation with description Generate synthetic samples for under-represented groups
Data Augmentation with long description "Create additional synthetic data points for minority classes or under-represented subgroups using interpolation or generative techniques. Addresses {risk} on {operator} without discarding majority-class samples."

Stratified Splitting is a Mitigation
Stratified Splitting with description Preserve class proportions across train and test splits
Stratified Splitting with long description "Replace {operator} with stratified splitting (stratify=y) or StratifiedKFold. Each fold or split preserves the original class distribution, preventing {risk} introduced by random splitting. Graph rewrite: add stratify parameter or swap for StratifiedKFold."

Feature Removal is a Mitigation
Feature Removal with description Drop proxy or sensitive features from the pipeline
Feature Removal with long description "Remove features identified as proxies for protected attributes upstream of {operator}. This addresses {risk} by preventing the model from learning through correlated sensitive attributes. Requires a feature importance analysis to identify which features to drop."

Reweighting is a Mitigation
Reweighting with description Assign higher sample weights to under-represented groups
Reweighting with long description "Compute sample weights inversely proportional to group frequency and pass them to {operator} via sample_weight. Alternatively set class_weight balanced. Reduces {risk} without modifying the training data itself."

Bias Auditing is a Mitigation
Bias Auditing with description Run fairness metrics on model predictions to quantify bias
Bias Auditing with long description "Add a post-training evaluation step after {operator} that computes fairness metrics (Disparate Impact, Statistical Parity Difference, Equal Opportunity Difference, Theil Index) using the AIF360 toolkit. This is a diagnostic mitigation that quantifies {risk} but does not automatically fix it."

Adversarial Debiasing is a Mitigation
Adversarial Debiasing with description Apply post-processing to equalize outcomes across groups
Adversarial Debiasing with long description "Insert a calibrated equalized-odds post-processor after {operator} that adjusts prediction probabilities to satisfy fairness constraints. Addresses {risk} using CalibratedEqOddsPostprocessing or RejectOptionClassification."

Cross Validation is a Mitigation
Cross Validation with description Replace hold-out split with k-fold cross validation
Cross Validation with long description "Replace {operator} with k-fold cross validation (KFold or StratifiedKFold) to prevent {risk}. Each fold trains on k-1 parts and validates on 1, giving a more robust performance estimate. Graph rewrite: replace the split sub-graph with a KFold iteration pattern."

Normalization Check is a Mitigation
Normalization Check with description Verify scaling is fitted on training data only
Normalization Check with long description "Ensure that {operator} is fitted exclusively on the training set and then applied (transform) to both train and test. Fitting on the full dataset before splitting causes information leakage and {risk}. The compound operator expansion (fit + transform) enforces this when properly wired."

Outlier Detection is a Mitigation
Outlier Detection with description Add an outlier detection step before scaling
Outlier Detection with long description "Insert an outlier detection node (IsolationForest, Z-score filter, or IQR clipping) before {operator}. Outliers disproportionately affect mean- and range-based scalers, causing {risk}. Graph rewrite: insert a filter node upstream of the scaler."

Feature Importance Analysis is a Mitigation
Feature Importance Analysis with description Inspect feature importances to detect shift or proxy features
Feature Importance Analysis with long description "Add a feature importance computation step (permutation importance, SHAP values, or tree-based importances) after {operator} to identify which features contribute most to predictions. Useful for detecting {risk}. Results are surfaced for manual review."

Class Weight Balancing is a Mitigation
Class Weight Balancing with description Set class_weight balanced on the classifier
Class Weight Balancing with long description "Configure {operator} to automatically adjust weights inversely proportional to class frequencies. Most sklearn estimators support class_weight balanced. Graph rewrite: add a class_weight Parameter node connected to {operator} with value balanced. This addresses {risk}."

Robust Scaling is a Mitigation
Robust Scaling with description Replace standard scaler with a robust scaler using median and IQR
Robust Scaling with long description "Swap {operator} with sklearn.preprocessing.RobustScaler, which uses the median and interquartile range instead of mean and standard deviation. This makes scaling resistant to outliers and addresses {risk}. Graph rewrite: replace the Operator node name from {operator} to sklearn.preprocessing.RobustScaler."

Missing Value Analysis is a Mitigation
Missing Value Analysis with description Audit the imputation strategy for missing-not-at-random patterns
Missing Value Analysis with long description "Analyse the missing-value pattern to distinguish MCAR, MAR and MNAR. If MNAR is detected, {operator} mean/median strategy may introduce {risk}. Consider model-based imputation (IterativeImputer) or indicator variables instead."

Direct Alternative is a Mitigation
Direct Alternative with description Replace {operator} with an equivalent operator without {risk}
Direct Alternative with long description "Replace {operator} with a semantically equivalent operator that performs the same data science task ({task}) but is not linked to {risk} in the knowledge base. Alternatives: {alternatives}."

# ==========================================================================
# Mitigation → Risk mappings (might_mitigate)
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Fairness mitigations ----
Resampling might mitigate Class Imbalance
Class Weight Balancing might mitigate Class Imbalance
Data Augmentation might mitigate Class Imbalance
Stratified Splitting might mitigate Sampling Bias
Stratified Splitting might mitigate Class Imbalance
Reweighting might mitigate Group Bias
Reweighting might mitigate Selection Bias
Feature Removal might mitigate Proxy Features
Feature Importance Analysis might mitigate Proxy Features
Bias Auditing might mitigate Algorithmic Bias
Bias Auditing might mitigate Historical Bias
Adversarial Debiasing might mitigate Algorithmic Bias
Adversarial Debiasing might mitigate Group Bias
Data Augmentation might mitigate Aggregation Bias

# ---- Robustness mitigations ----
Normalization Check might mitigate Distribution Shift
Normalization Check might mitigate Feature Scaling Bias
Cross Validation might mitigate Data Leakage
Cross Validation might mitigate Overfitting
Outlier Detection might mitigate Outlier Bias
Robust Scaling might mitigate Outlier Bias
Robust Scaling might mitigate Distribution Shift
Feature Importance Analysis might mitigate Covariate Shift

# ---- Transparency mitigations ----
Missing Value Analysis might mitigate Measurement Bias
Bias Auditing might mitigate Label Noise

# ==========================================================================
# Rewrite rule metadata — ontological relationships
#
# Rule bodies (pattern + transformations) live in ``expdb.rewrites``
# collection.  The KB declares which parameters each mitigation exposes
# so that the compiler can resolve signature information.
#
# Mitigations without a rule doc in expdb are diagnostic-only (toast).
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Parameter signatures ----
Class Weight Balancing has parameter class_weight
Stratified Splitting has parameter stratify
Reweighting has parameter class_weight
class_weight is of type str
stratify is of type str
